value.0: This hearty stout from Arabel is one of the city's major exports, and deservedly so.  best served at cellar temperature (Arabellans sniff at any other way of serving this drink), this stout is heavy and jet black with a dark brown head of foam.
A Sembian brew of strong, harsh temperament, dragon's breath is often served with a platter of dark rye bread and death cheese.

A delicate, slighly sweet wine made from honey, mead is slow to ferment and in scarce supply compared to grape wines or those of other fruits.  Mead from the fantastic honey bees that inhabit the gardens in Neverwinter is said to be the finest in the North.

Indigenous to the North, this unusual wine is a purplish-blue in hue, often leading to jokes that the grapes "caught a chill."  This is quite true, as the grapes are allowed to freeze on the vine.  They are then harvested and crushed while still frozen.
This good wine, red or white, is often bought in bulk as provisioning for a tavern, castle, or manor.  It supplies a merry evening and is unfailingly tasty.

Typically from Calimshan and Tethyr, spiced wine is a taste treat and a sovereign remedy for many ailments, including nausea, cough, and huskiness of the throat.  Raisin, cinnamon, fennel, anise, nutmeg and clove varieties are available.
This good wine is often bought in bulk as provisioning for a tavern, castle, or manor.  It supplies a merry evening and is unfailingly tasty.

This bitter drink is brewed from beans brought from the continent of Maztica by Amnish explorers.  It is a stimulating tonic, though it can make one jittery as well.

Its rarity makes the price somewhat high.
This is a domestic ale - not too fancy or flavorful, but it gets the job done.
Taken from farm-raised cows, milk is both delicious and nutritious.
This is a pre-made jug of herbal tea.
This is a domestic bottle of spirits - not too fancy or flavorful, but it gets the job done.
Although colorless, odorless, and tasteless, water is thirst-quenching and needed for life.  Many city-folk who do not live near a well or river must purchase water from a market.
Produced from cow's milk, cheese is a delicious food that goes well with a good wine.
This bowl contains a hot broth mixed with pieces of meat and assorted vegetables.
Eggs are a wonderful source of protein.
A light snack to be eaten between meals or while in a hurry.
Fresh greens provide a wonderful source of nutrients.
Bread is the staple food of the commoner, both filling and nutritious.
Assorted nuts are good sources of nutrition.
This run-of-the-mill meal isn't the finest fare in Faern, but nourishing and filling nonetheless.
